## Extensible Future Features (designed for, not building now)

### EX-01 · Multi-Tenant SaaS

- Organization isolation (row-level security in Postgres)
- Billing tiers with usage quotas (reviews/month)
- Admin portal for org management
- API keys per org

### EX-02 · Additional Language Support

- Java, Go, Rust, C++ via tree-sitter grammar additions
- Language-specific rule packs per agent
- Architecture: adding a language is one grammar file + one embedding config

### EX-03 · Custom Rule Sets (per-repo YAML)

- `.pr-review.yml` config in repo root
- Define custom patterns, disable specific rules, set severity overrides
- Rule versioning and inheritance

### EX-04 · Notifications (Slack / Teams / Email)

- Webhook-out to Slack channel on review completion
- Configurable: only notify on Critical/High findings

### EX-05 · Auto-Fix Pull Requests

- For simple, deterministic findings (e.g. missing null check, unused import), auto-open a fix PR
- Human-in-the-loop approval before push

### EX-06 · Developer & Team Analytics

- Per-developer issue frequency trends
- Team-wide code quality dashboard over time
- Issue category breakdown by repo

### EX-07 · Multi-Platform VCS Support

- GitLab MR integration (same pipeline, different API adapters)
- Bitbucket PR integration
- Architecture: VCS platform is an interface; GitHub is the first implementation

### EX-08 · CI/CD Gate Integration

- GitHub Actions status check that blocks merge if Critical/High findings exceed threshold
- Configurable threshold per repo

### EX-09 · False Positive Feedback Loop

- Developers dismiss individual comments with a reason
- Dismissed comments logged; used to fine-tune agent prompts or adjust severity calibration

### EX-10 · Fine-Tuned / Org-Specific Models

- Fine-tune on org's historical PR review data
- Custom severity calibration per org based on their coding standards

### EX-11 · Pre-Commit IDE Plugin

- VS Code extension that runs SecurityAgent + ArchAgent on staged diff before commit
- Requires local model or API key

### EX-12 · PR Complexity Scoring

- ML-based complexity metrics (churn, coupling change, test coverage delta)
- Review effort estimation surfaced in the PR review summary
